Italy Finance Minister Tremonti Won’t Resign, Corriere Reports

-- B y   A r m o r e l   K e n n a
-- 
2011-09-24T10:33:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-24/italy-finance-minister-tremonti-won-t-resign-corriere-reports.html
Italian Finance Minister  Giulio Tremonti  doesn’t plan to resign, Corriere della Sera reported.  “They haven’t got the tools to get rid of me,” the
newspaper cited Tremonti as saying.  Italian Prime Minister  Silvio Berlusconi  considered a move
to end Tremonti’s relationship with the government, while
Undersecretary Gianni Letta stopped him, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Armorel Kenna in Milan at 
 akenna@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net  